ught behind sow on bottom of buffs is that those classes that dispel or use pumice even will have to get through all your buffs first before your sow gets canceled.<br><br>if he's  smart ranger he'll dispell you with pumice and also dispell your dots...ya know what i could go on and on about this. do the following and you have  good chance of winning:<br><br>since this is a duel to the death and i'm guessin there will be no zone hopping etc here are the spells to have memmed and buffs to have up:<br><br>Buffs:<br>1) blank<br>2) blank<br>3) Firefist<br>4) Strength<br>5) See Invis<br>6) SoW<br>7) Bramblecoat<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Resist Cold<br>9) Resist Fire<br>10)Skin Like Steel<br>11)Regen<br>12)Shield of Brambles<br>13)Regen<br>14)Levitate<br>15)Endure Magic<br><br>spells:<br>1) Greater Healing<br>2) SoW<br>3) Ensnare<br>3) Drones<br>4) Immolate<br>5) Combust<br>6) Shield of Brambles<br>7) Cancel Magic<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Invis/Root (not sure how invis works on bluebie server with duels, if he loses targeting cuz of it then great if not then don't use it) if u land ensare then no need for root<br><br><br>Ensare, Ensare, Ensnare (hope it sticks after 3 tries..if not you probalby not gonna stick it)<br>Drones<br>Immolate<br>Combust, Combust, so on and so forth<br><br>Don't be afraid to trade blows with him with your DS and regen in the beginning , especially if u get snare to stick...anyway write alot about this but do the above and you should be fine.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umoridinthemad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moridin the Mad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/25/02 12:11:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all of your input guys, your wisdom is much appreciated =).  I do have another question, thought.  How much of a difference does level make, if say, he is 3 levels higher than me? (Me being lvl 34, he being 37, or 35 and 38, etc).  Does that give him much advantage? <p><hr><img src="http://www.infinitysys.net/images/ezsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulaurenia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laurenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/25/02 8:43:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> the level difference WILL affect root. it always does, and root is very unreliable anyway...so that gets rid of the root strategy. but your Drones dot will stick all the time, and dont forget to tell us his equip types....what are his resists? :P once you know THAT, hes toast <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC = "http://laurenia.homestead.com/files/laurenia_sig_final.jpg" WIDTH=383 HEIGHT=223  BORDER=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualudiwensomeshta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aludiwen Someshta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font