m 100% certain.) <br>-Combust <br>As a finisher only, or if your mana level &gt; his HP level. Druids don't have the mana to chain nuke someone down in my experience.<br><br>Things that may happen during the duel:<br>-Your friend is smart and DISPELS drones of doom.<br>Ok it's not over yet, do not try and land drones anymore because this is a waste of mana. Damage shield yourself and go toe to toe. If you know how to joust that's even better.<br><br>-Your friend is even smarter and instead of killing himself on your damage shield, he switches to 2HS.<br>Ok it's looking bad now, but what I suggest is:<br>Try to stack dummy buffs on him (endure cold, endure fire, endure poison ... fast cast low mana buffs) and then DoT him again with Drones. If he tries to dispel go into melee to interrupt. Make sure you stay out of melee range when pumice / cancel magic ends casting, hybrids have no delay when casting spells and his hit will land right after.<br><br>-Your friend realizes he can just click off said buffs and then go for the dot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Well now this is just bad. All I can say to this is to try and wear him down with a combination of nukes, melee / thistles and regen. Pull back if you still have sow. If not, I hope you have Spirit of Cheetah memmed for a quick escape.<br><br>Unless your friend has simply terrible resist gear, druids are not meant to be a quick kill class. You wear down your opponent slowly and by the time they realize they are going to die, that last nuke is coming their way.<br><br>Last note, my recommended spell list:<br>1) Greater Healing<br>2) Drones of Doom<br>3) Spirit of Cheetah (once you get away demem this and swap in SoW for duration)<br>4) Ensnare<br>5) Combust<br>6) Ro's Fiery Sundering<br>7) Shield of Brambles<br>8 ) Dunno, be creative. Usually would be gate but if this is a fight to the finish, use whatever.<br><br>bah I know I said last point, but here's another tip: make sure you know where every spell is in your spellbook. When you get distance, type in /book # to quickly go to that page and mem the spell you're looking for. Critical for any class that has so much utility like druids. <p>Greyof<br><a href="http://www.honorbound.vze.com"><img src="http://server27.hypermart.net/stray/HBLogo.jpg "></a><br>See my <a href="http://www.geocities.com/greyofsz/">Kill Galleries!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugielgiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giel Giel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/31/02 11:35:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid VS Ranger</span><hr size=1> omg, don't let some punk chanter from Honorbound tell you how to play your dr00d.  read my stuff instead<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>because Honorbound sucks!<br><br>I think you get the point among the various posts and on a side not..our fire debuff of Ro's is a lvl 39 spell, so please excuse the HB enchanter who recommended you cast that on him when you are sub-39.<br><br>/poke Greyof <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugreysz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GreySZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/8/02 8:19:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </